## Git Safety

The agents commit checkpoints automatically. You can also:

```bash
# See what changed
git diff
git log --oneline -10

# Revert everything back to last commit
git checkout -- .

# Revert a specific file
git checkout -- path/to/file

# See all tags
git tag -l
```

---

## Tips

- **Push back.** If the orchestrator proposes something you disagree with, say so.
- **Redirect mid-session.** "Stop working on X. Switch to Y." works fine.
- **Ask why.** "Why did you choose that?" forces justification.
- **Request the scrutinizer.** If things feel stale, say "have the scrutinizer challenge everything."
- **Fresh sessions are fine.** After 3-5 heavy cycles, start fresh.

